==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Mucic
<hw>Mu"cic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>mucus</ets>
mucus: cf. F. <ets>mucique</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>Pertaining to, or derived from, gums and micilaginous substances;
specif., denoting an acid obtained by the oxidation of gums, dulcite,
etc., as a white crystalline substance isomeric with saccharic
acid.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mucid</ent>⟦br⟧
